  Locus:
    Page: 118
    Verse: 5
Tags:
  - Ego
---
The ego thinks from a small standpoint in the center. It thinks outward. It
seeks to know by groping in the unknown, attempting to rationalize what it
finds there. Since infinite space surrounds it, it is impossible for it to
ever grow into great understanding.
